  <subsection>
    <title>Function Transformations</title>
    <p>
      In <xref ref="PA_0_3">Preview Activity</xref> we experimented with the four main types of function
      transformations. You no doubt noticed that the values of <m>C</m> and <m>D</m> <em>shift</em> the
      parent function and the values of <m>A</m> and <m>B</m> <em>stretch</em> the parent function. More
      descriptively, if <m>f(x)</m> is a parent function and
      <me>
        F(x) = Af(B(x-C))+D
